#summary Overview of SSPxxx registers per PIC

----

= Overview of SSPxxx registers per PIC =

Based on MPLAB version 8.80

The names of the SSP registers are those to be found in the device
files: 'normalized' like documented in 'devicefiles.html',
but <b>without aliases</b>.
<br>Multi-bit fields which take the whole register are not enumerated.
Multi-bit fields smaller than 8 bits are enumerated, like in the datasheets.
In the device files multi-bit fields are mostly declared as single variable!
<br>Double names (like D/NA, R/NW) are not splitted here, unlike in the device files.

This wiki may contains PICs for which there is no Jallib device file yet!

<i>This wiki may be extended later after more analysis.</i>
